# Change discipline

- Touch only what the task requires; if it works, do not rewrite it.
- Preserve existing public behavior and response shapes unless the task says otherwise.
- Read the full file (and nearby callers) before editing.
- One focused fix at a time; avoid drive-by renames or framework churn.
- Do not invent libraries, env vars, or APIs without evidence in the repo.
- If uncertain after inspecting the code, ask the user instead of guessing.

# Project fit

- Match naming, folder layout, and patterns already used in `app/` and `lib/`.
- Do not add new UI kits or state libraries unless the user asks.
